caption: We ordered through DoorDash for pickup and got several items from the Dim Sum menu. It was all fantastic! The pan fried potstickers are so good, the shrimp dumplings were PACKED with tons of huge shrimp. Everything was hot and tasted great will definitely be ordering from them again. Get the Dim Sum you can’t go wrong and it’s priced so well!

This food was crazy good...it really hit the spot. Dim sum is freshly made and great quality, this is not your average cook-from-frozen dimsum a lot of other places have. If you live on the northside you can save a trip to Chinatown and just get D Cuisine, its as good or better.  I got the shrimp dumpling, steam bbq pork bun, egg custard bun, stir fried sticky rice, and beef chow fun. Everything was authentic and delicious. Haven't had food this good in a long time.
We really enjoyed our meal!  Tasty & delicious.  Highly Recommend.

I absolutely cannot stress how good our food was! If you are vegetarian like me, you HAVE to order the sautéed bean curd skin with broccoli and shallots. It is out of this world. Their vegetable fried rice was also very good.  I had previously gone for dim sum and wasn’t too impressed. Order off their regular food menu for the best food!

Ordered a dinner for my daughter who is a front line doctor who had to work today...Christmas Day..wanted her to come home and relax!!! We both got an email at 6:55pm...her order was to arrive. She then got a text from restaurant that they were going to go ahead and deliver the meal themselves. This restaurant went way beyond what was expected. I will go here again but I will not use the delivery service...they are the ones that cancelled...the company was HG...

My experience was horrible with D Cuisine! I ordered directly from the restaurant’s website for a future order at 10:15 am pick up on Saturday, Dec 5th. I ordered at 9:35 am and the website said that 10:15 am was available for pick up. Restaurant listed online and on window of restaurant that they are opened at 8 am. The time they actually opened is at 10:30 am. I have called in the past to order my food and someone mentioned that they will be opened at 10 am.  Unfortunately, I arrived at 10:10 am and the lights were off and the D Cuisine was NOT opened. It finally opened at 10:30 am.  I got there and asked if my 10:15 am order was ready for pick up, the young woman worker-CiCi stated that it will be another 15 minutes. First, I was promised 10:15 am. Second, they charged my credit card already. My order was paid for. Third, I had to deal with an unprofessional CiCi who just said that she came late to work and sorry for being late. I asked for the manager's name. CiCi refused to give me her manger’s name or contact information.  Regardless, if you are open or not, don’t allow customers to order ahead on your direct website if you are going to be late or not open until 30 mins after the stated time.  When I came back after 15 mins like CiCi said, she said my turnip cakes were not ready yet. I overheard her speaking Cantonese to the cook and stated that I was “arrogant” customer. I am not arrogant because I called you on being 30 mins late to work. Making a paying customer wait 33 mins extra when you promise food at a specific time and to call a customer "arrogant" in a different language does not make it okay. This is unacceptable.  I spoke back to her Cantonese instead of English. CiCi was surprised that I spoke fluent Cantonese. Not only was CiCi being unprofessional for showing up late but to call a paying customer "arrogant" is not acceptable regardless if you think I don't spoke the language or not.  Finally , I got my order at 10:48 am, 33 mins after the promised time and CiCi who refuses to give me the manager’s name. This is unprofessional and unacceptable. I will make sure, I contact the BBB about the horrible service I received.  I later called D Cuisine around 8 pm, to find the manager of D Cuisine. CiCi answered and told me that Benny was the name of the manager and he was not at the restaurant currently. About 1 hour later, Benny gives me a call and poor excuses for the misleading information out there opening times and excuses for the lateness of CiCi. He informed me that CiCi is actually the OWNER OF D CUISINE! I was shocked by this. How do you have the OWNER asking their manager to call me back, when clearly she could have handled it because you are the owner. I wanted to support local businesses during pandemic, but this experience makes it hard to do so.  I told Benny how unprofessional and unacceptable this experience was. He refunded my order, but if this was handled properly to begin with, this should have been done right when I got my food at 10:48 am (33 minutes after promised time).
Ordered takeout from here. Portions are small. The food was bland and unappetizing. Will not return.
Took too long for food and they became very cold.

Ordered D Cuisine because wanted to check it out. Got the chicken fried rice, sweet and sour chicken, egg rolls, and pot stickers! Everything was really tasty. I definitely enjoyed and would order again! Good addition to the neighborhood!

Best Cantonese food in Chicago. As a Cantonese myself, I'm always so picky about dim sum and Canton food. And the chef here KNOWS how to make authentic Cantonese food. Must try: egg tarts, egg yolk buns, bbq pork buns, dried scallop & egg white fried rice, beef chow fun.

Had the baked cha sui bao (roast pork)  (!) Honestly the bread layer is so delicate and the filling is delicious. Had a lot of cha sui baos in my life, and this is prob one of the most memorable ones I’ve had. Also it’s part of their dim sum weekly special. You must.

Yah this restaurant has it going on. The dim sum dishes were all really excellent and very fresh. Great flavor and the right amount of spice - but be careful spicy means spicy. i always ask for mild. The best thing us the flavor and the freshness. Yum - but also take care the place is often packed.
They're always amazing and kind there.
Wow this place is legit.  Def my new go to spot for Chinese takeout.

Food was good when they first opened. My families eat there and order take out very often. I am Asian and it was very nice to finally get a small menu of dim sum in Lakeview East. I ordered take-out on June 15 and spent over $70 dollars there. Dim sum was ok but the food was so gross. Greasy, bad quality and taste like something you order from a Chinese fast food restaurant. I feel like I waste $70 dollars and throw away a lot of food.
Love that they serve dim sum all day. While the dim sum selection isn't huge, the quality is top notch. We also like their enters, especially there bbq roast pork.
Excellent. Great food, great atmosphere, great service. An easy, and purely enjoyable experience.
Great dim sum. Lots of amazing seafood! The shrimp dumplings were bomb. Fast & friendly service too. Will definitely go back.
Good food.  BYOB is a plus.

We tried this restaurant out when running errands and shopping in Lakeview and this turned out to be the perfect place for a quick yet sumptuous meal. The dim sums we ordered were delicious but the highlight really was the service. It was incredibly quick without feeling rushed. The server brought us some tea and then refilled the tea pot with hot water within 15 minutes. Plates, when emptied, were carted off the table within a minute. Highly efficient with no compromise on the quality/taste of food.

The staff was great and very friendly (so 3 stars for the staff)..  but i dont know if its just our luck or not but I went with 3 other family members for dim sum around 2:30pm.. And a few hours later.. 3/4 we got food poisoning after eating here.. we we're constantly vomiting for 2 days.. and after that it is TMI to write... but this is the only place we ate at that whole day.
Very good dim sum

I’m so happy there is a dim sum place in our local area. They have a more limited dim sum menu yet that shouldn’t deter you. The Egg Yolk Buns are my favorite. Our table was very happy with the portions, taste, and menu offerings. Service was prompt and helpful.
So happy I don't have to drive to Chinatown for good dim sum anymore!
Good food. Don't miss the dim-sum.  Very bright dinning area, not my cup of tea.
Can't believe they offer dimsum really early! Food was great, service was awesome!

Wow! Loved this place. So happy to have checked it out and even happier that it’s just a block from home. Highlights of the meal included the green chive dumplings, shu mai, and Singapore noodles (which were full of perfect curry and heat!). Was also loving the simple, and comforting, chicken fried rice. Also do not leave without trying the baked creamy egg yolk buns (it’s dessert!).
Love it, very good food, nice service and atmosphere. I highly reccomended

NOT BAD.  On the north side and don't feel like making your way down to Chinatown for dim sum or some noodles? Look no further. D Cuisine got you covered. We were pleasantly surprised but the food. On Sundays, street parking on Clark is free and no hassle finding a spot mid afternoon. Yay! Unlike some of the grungier places you'll find in Chinatown, inside D Cuisine is modern, sleek, and CLEAN.  For food, started with an order of siu mai. While it was past normal dim sum hours they were still able to make a fresh order for us. Very good!  In addition, also did a veggie dish (snow pea tips) topped with fried tofu. Pretty good! And an order of black bean and pepper beef chow fun. Not bad either. Lastly, the salt & pepper fish fillet was what I was craving most, but sadly it was the most disappointing of all the dishes we ordered. Way too much batter/breading. :'(  Aside from the fish fillet, still an overall solid spot and will save me a trip from going all the way down to Chinatown.  'Til next time.
Interesting food selections. Really good food. Enough to take home
That was the only open place on Clark Street on XMAS 2019
Best Chinese restaurant outside of Chinatown.

Their food is not bad, but they use MSG in all their dim sum - which is completely unnecessary, given the quality of ingredients they use. If they would reconsider the use of MSG in their food, I'd be more than happy to engage with them again, but it's becoming increasingly difficult to go back.  Siu Mai, Crabmeat Wrap w/ Seaweed, Guangzhou Style Roast Chicken. Har Gao ingredients are good, but skin is thick.
Dim sum all hours!  Great service, reasonably priced.

I love dim sum but don't want to go out early on a weekend to get it. Passed by this place last time I was in Lakeview and it made me want to go in and try it but I wasn't the slightest bit hungry then. Luckily the next time I was in Lakeview I was hungry and there were empty tables that were filling up at a steady pace. We ordered a few dim sum dishes and I ordered a vegetable main dish as Chinese vegetables are well-suited to my tastes. I ordered Dry Pot Cauliflower with meat paste and it came out at the end of the meal. I was initially dismayed to see whole chilies and chili flakes in the dish since even though I enjoy spicy food I can no longer eat it very well. It was sizzling in its pot and came with rice for both of us. The cauliflower looked closee to romesco in color but whatever kind they used it was delicious. There wasn't a lot of meat but the dish had a fantastic flavor and not too much heat. I look forward to going back to try other chef's specialties on the menu but I will also definitely be ordering this again.
Pricey and ok on dim sum and stir fry.

I really liked the foods and service here. Reasonable prices and clean place. My friend’s wife is from China who tries different Chinese restaurants in Chicago. I asked her how do you like this place. She mentioned “she would give it 4 out of five!”
Great dim sum, lovely decor and service. We'll definitely be back!
Fabulous food beautifully presented. Service is friendly; atmosphere is conversationally friendly.
Great food, great service, insane value. So relaxing inside. Will be back.
Quality food, very nice atmosphere if you are looking for honest food in a low key but pleasant environment.

So thrilled to have a dim sum spot in the neighborhood. This place hit the spot for my frequent dim sum cravings without making the trip to chinatown. I came for brunch on a Saturday and there were plenty of open tables, service was quick, and food was fresh. The selection is a bit more slim than your Ming Hin but that’s to be expected for a smaller shop, regardless they had all the must haves. Would recommend!
Dim sum is a must eat!!

Excited to see a new dimsum place in the neighborhood! Had an OK experience for our first time visiting. Shortribs were a smaller portion and than at other local popular dimsum spots, and were mushy and greybrown, not well grilled on the outside. Fried shrimp rolls were nicely golden and soft, with good taste. Egg yolk buns were a bit dry and the entire bottom was baked onto the baking paper. Business was steady even in a light rain, and hope to revisit and try the dinner menu items. Maybe it is still growing pains for a new business, but for now I will stick to Chinatown for dependable dimsum.
Great dim sum and friendly, prompt service.  I especially enjoyed the sweet corn and chicken soup and the Siu Mai was delicious.
Tried to come for dim sum Saturday morning per the hours posted online and on the store front but found it was closed. Extremely disappointing as I was hoping to try it out.

Great experience here for lunch today!  Nice to see a bit of dim sum in Lincoln Park.  Prices are super reasonable and all dim sum was freshly cooked (nice and hot)!  Great service.  We had hoped for a small portion of veggies for dim sum, but it's not on the menu.  Oh well.  To our surprise, the waiter brought us a small dish of chinese broccoli with oyster sauce complimentary.  It was nice to have some greens!  Hahah.  My only recommendation would be to add a small plate vegetable option to the dim sum menu.  Will absolutely be back!
I really liked this place!!!
Very good food and friendly service!!

I came in for some Friday morning dim sum. I was met with a smile as the hostess was very friendly. I ordered quite a bit of food. All of it was delicious. I enjoyed every bite. The pork bun and pot stickers really stood out.

Awesome place for dim sum close to home, when Furama or Chinatown are just a little too much of a trek. Every dish we got was delicious, and service was very attentive. We all ate until we were totally stuffed and the bill ended up at less than $20 each. I will be back!

FINALLY...a GREAT Chinese restaurant with delicious food and healthy ingredients (yes they use organic bamboo shoots) in our area. We no longer have to go down town or to China Town. Also, the staff is very attentive, friendly and accommodating. Highly recommend this place!

5 STARS!! Yes, if you don't want to drive to Chinatown or fly to China for REALLY Authentic Chinese food, that is nourishing, comforting, DELICIOUS, fun and diverse flavor and appetite, go, go, go to D-Cuisine. Vegan/vegetarian/food allergy awareness friendly!!!  Or you are SUPER HUNGRY & not waste time trying  to figure out what to eat, or just want high quality food, high quality service with your waiter, Go. I ordered the vegetarian clay pot tofu with mustard green & mushrooms: yum, yum and yum. I'm a super foodie and this place will make sure you are happy before, during and after you eat there! Treat yourself and be good to yourself: you will accomplish alot just by eating here.

Where has this place been my whole life?  Love the food here.  The employees are amazing.  They are so helpful and were beyond accommodating.   This will be our go to spot for Chinese and dim sum north of downtown.  Will probably go back a few times just this week.  Plus, this is place such a peaceful and beautiful decor.

Great location. Really friendly waitresses and beautiful comfortable interior. The Chinese art and furniture was unique and the decor was breathtaking. They offer affordable delicious authentic Chinese food. My favorite part is that you get to choose between black tea and green tea. It is a BYOB establishment so you are welcome to bring your own drinks. I encourage you to meet friends there it's a great location to have a business meeting or an intimate conversation. The bathrooms are clean. And you're able to take out food.

After seeing a heap of praise from the Chicago Tribune, had.to check it out.  Very good!  Ranging from smaller Dim Sum to substantial  entrees, the menu is varied and highlights some unique looking dishes. First ti.e I,  tried the Sweet Corn and Chicken soup (could use a hit of salt and white pepper, but very good), Black.Pepper and Honey ribs (very tasty), Classic Pot Stickers (awesome) and Shrimp Dumplings, which were perfectly cooked.  Will check.it.out again and soon

Super authentic Chinese food - the dim-sum are amazing - the baked creamy yolk buns are to die for. Their regular menu is really good, and authentic too! We love the Chive with preserved meat!!  The decoration is more higher-end and the service is pleasant. It's slightly more expensive than Chinatown, but the food, service, decoration and the fact we are in the heart of Lincoln Park explains that.  The clients are a mix of locals and Chinese families.
Easily the best Cantonese restaurant in the Lincoln Park/Lakeview area. Dim Sum from 8am!

GROSS. The other reviews have to be fake. The dim sum selection was almost rancid, it had to have been made at least a day before and reheated throughout the day. Flavorless heap of gross seafood. The pork bun was incredibly dry. To top it off there was a lipstick stain on my cup.The worst Chinese food I have ever eaten. Please go elsewhere.

We ordered Siu Mai, Shrimp Dumpling, Egg Rolls, Egg Drop Soup & Mongolian Beef and everything was really really but really good! This place is super neat, great decor & the customer service is the best.

Stopped in for lunch...delicious hot and sour soup! They also make a mean hot and spicy jumbo shrimp dish, with super-generous portions. Pillowy white rice served piping hot. A lovely spot. (And...the Chicago Tribune loved it!)
excellent food. a very upscale classy décor at regular prices. I had beef mei fun but next time the braised dive looks interesting. They have an extensive menu and the service is in the classic style
D Cuisine, stand up and take a bao. The meal we had was all that and Dim Sum.
Good place you need to go

Great Dim Sum in Lincoln Park, they open at 8AM everyday! If you're looking for good dim sum spot that's inexpensive, check this place out. Located on Clark St by Diversey, if you want some good Siu Mai or BBQ pork buns, this place is a must try. My favorite was the shrimp dumpling, full of shrimp in a thin rice paper, I could of eaten 3 orders of those, it was delicious. Fairly new but I will be taking visiting friends there for brunch, great for groups and everything is shareable.
Very good! Happy to have found a good dim sum place in the area! The egg tarts were amazing
So delicious! The waiters are super attentive,too.
Excellent
Great service from the staff and best Chinese food I’ve had in the city.
Good food, the staff was very attentive. In my neighborhood so I will definitely return!
Beautiful decor, great selection of in-house sauces, my beef short ribs just arrive gotta go!!!😋😋😋
Great food and service!!! We will come back!
Delicious and fresh
The space is very inviting, friendly staff and servers. The dim sum was delicious and the dinner as well. Good servings. Plenty of food to share.

Ate here twice in one week and have zero regrets. Welcome to Lakeview, authentic HK Chinese food!!  For dinner, don’t sleep on the black bean pepper beef and chow fun - it’s one of the best things I’ve never had before and now love. Texture is pretty magical and I’ll be coming back for it again. Dim sum is decent but I’m eagerly waiting for them to add shrimp crepe noodles, wrapped sticky rice with pork / chicken (hint hint) and expand the breakfast menu with even more goodies. That said, I’ll take what I can get in the meantime!

I dropped in for an impromptu dinner because I saw it was a new place. Sat at the bar and was taken care of immediately. Super tasty dim sum (BBQ pork buns, crab/seaweed fried roll) and enjoyed the Black Pepper Asparagus and Chicken entrée. Will return!  Note: no drink or cocktail menu so it might be BYOB
Great food and nice and quiet place to dine. Superb atmosphere, attentive staff. No need to go to Chinatown!
Too expensive for dim sum. Furama isn't far from here at 1/2 the price
Went to lunch and LOVED it!!!! Super good dim sum and friendly staff! I'm excited they are Lakeview!!!

So happy this place opened up close to home! Delicious dim sum, all were piping hot when served and the textures/flavors were just right. Other than dim sum, there is also a great variety of both Americanized and authentic Chinese entrees.

Attentive service with very fresh authentic cantonese dim sum (small plates), along with a wide selection of Chinese American favorites. Will be back and excited to have this as an addition to the neighborhood.
